{{Infobox Archbishop |honorific-prefix = [[His Beatitude]] |name = Christopher |archbishop_of = [[Archbishop of Albania]] |image = Archbishop Kristofor Kisi.jpg |enthroned = 1937 |ended = 1948 |predecessor = [[Visarion Xhuvani]] |successor = [[Paisius of Albania]] |birth_name = Kristofor Kisi |birth_date = 1881 |birth_place = [[Berat]], [[Albania]] (then [[Ottoman Empire]]) |death_date = 16 June 1958<ref>[http://www.seda.org.al/download/i/mark_dl/u/4012653116/4611166555/2.4-Religion.pdf]</ref> |death_place = |alma_mater = }} {{Infobox manner of address | background = plum | name = The Archbishop of Tirana, Durrës and all Albania | image = [[File:Kisha Ortodokse e Shqipërisë.svg|80px]] | reference = His Beatitude | spoken = Your Beatitude | religious = Archbishop | posthumous = N/A }} '''Archbishop Christopher of Albania''' ({{lang-sq|Kryepeshkopi Kristofori i Shqipërisë}}, secular name '''Sotir Kissi'''; 1881, [[Berat]] - June 16, 1959) was the primate of the [[Orthodox Autocephalous Church of Albania]] from 1937 to 1948. In 1959 he was found dead by poison.
==Biography== Kisi was born in [[Berat]] in 1881. In 1937 he became the primate of the [[Orthodox Autocephalous Church of Albania]] as successor of [[Visarion Xhuvani]], as authorized by the [[Patriarchate of Constantinople]], which recognized the [[Holy Synod]] of the Church of Albania in April 1937. During World War II Kisi backed up the initiative of Italy and the Vatican (subsequently aborted) to unite the Orthodox Church with the [[Eastern Catholic Churches|Uniate Church]].<ref name="Leustean2009">{{cite book|author=Lucian Leustean|title=Eastern Christianity and the Cold War, 1945-91|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2oOht_5bg6UC&pg=PA144|date=22 December 2009|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-203-86594-1|page=144}}</ref> Kisi and the [[Orthodox Autocephalous Church of Albania|OACA]] high hierarchy, in contrast to the stand of many Orthodox clergy and laity, were supportive to the anti-Communist resistance movement after World War II and had previously welcomed the decision from [[Albania under Nazi Germany|German authorities]] of extending the jurisdiction of Albanian church to the [[Eparchy of Raška and Prizren|Diocese of Prizren]] and newly created bishoprics of [[Peshkopi]]a and [[Struga]].
Kisi was found dead, as a result of poisoning, in 1958. His place as a primate was taken by Communist regime faithful, [[Pais Vodica]].<ref name=ARCT>{{cite news|last=Rehabilitation Centre for Trauma and Torture Albania|title=Genocidi Mbi Elitën Intelektuale të Kombit Shqiptar|url=http://www.arct.org/pdf/genocidi-241-270.pdf}}</ref>
