{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Use British English|date=June 2016}} {{infobox football biography | name = Edward Brueton | image = | fullname = | height = | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | birth_date = 1871 | birth_place = [[Penn, West Midlands|Penn]], England | death_date = | death_place = [[Wolverhampton]], England | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] | years2 = 1894 | clubs2 = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 1894–???? | clubs3 = [[Willenhall F.C.|Willenhall Swifts]] }} '''Edward Brueton''' (1871 – after 1893) was an English [[association football|footballer]] born in [[Penn, West Midlands|Penn]], [[Staffordshire]], who played in [[the Football League]] as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Small Heath]].<ref name=Joyce>{{cite book |last=Joyce |first=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939 |publisher=SoccerData |location=Nottingham |year=2004 |page=40 |isbn=978-1-899468-67-6}}</ref> He joined Small Heath from [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] on trial in September 1894. Without even playing [[reserve team]] football,<ref name=Matthews76>{{cite book |last=Matthews |first=Tony |title=Birmingham City: A Complete Record |year=1995 |publisher=Breedon Books |location=Derby |page=76 |isbn=978-1-85983-010-9}}</ref> he stood in for regular goalkeeper [[Charles Partridge]] in the home game against [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] on 29 September, conceded four goals&nbsp;– the game finished as a 4–4 draw<ref>Matthews, p. 142.</ref>&nbsp;– and was back in [[non-league football]] with [[Willenhall F.C.|Willenhall Swifts]] by November.<ref name=Matthews76/>
