nd anti-racism campaigner * [[Tom Cornell]] – American anti-war activist, initiated first anti-Vietnam War protest * [[Rachel Corrie]] (1979–2003) – American activist for Palestinian human rights{{sfn|Haaretz|2003}}{{sfn|BBC News|2012}} * [[David Cortright]] – American anti-nuclear weapon leader * [[Norman Cousins]] (1915–1990) – journalist, author, organizer, initiator * [[Randal Cremer]] (1828–1908) – British trade unionist and [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] (1885-95, 1900-08); pacifist; leading advocate for international arbitration; co-founded the [[Inter-Parliamentary Union]] and the [[International Arbitration League]]; promoted the [[Hague Conventions of 1899 and 1907|Hague Peace Conferences of 1899 and 1907]]; awarded Nobel Peace Prize (1903) * [[Frances Crowe]] (born 1919) – anti-war and [[anti-nuclear]] power, draft counselor * [[Adam Curle]] (1916–2006) – Quaker peace activist; first professor of [[peace studies]] in the UK :{{small|[[#toc|''return to table of contents'']]}}
