'''Per Knut Aaland''' (born 5 September 1954) is a retired [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[cross-country skier]].

He was born in [[Randabygda]], lived in [[Hornindal]] and represented the sports club [[Hardbagg IL]].<ref name=nrk>{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://www.nrk.no/sfj/leksikon/index.php/Per_Knut_Aaland|title=Per Knut Aaland|encyclopedia=Sogn og Fjordane fylkesleksikon|publisher=Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation|language=Norwegian|accessdate=29 March 2010}}</ref> He won a silver medal in the 4 x 10&nbsp;km relay at the [[Cross-country skiing at the 1980 Winter Olympics|1980 Olympic Games]] in [[Lake Placid, New York]]. He also finished sixth in the 50&nbsp;km race at the [[Cross-country skiing at the 1976 Winter Olympics|1976 Olympic Games]] and sixteenth in the 30&nbsp;km race at the 1980 Olympic Games.<ref name=sref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/aa/per-knut-aaland-1.html|title=Per Knut Aaland|publisher=Sports-Reference.com|accessdate=29 March 2010}}</ref> His best career finish was second in three World Cup events.<ref>{{FIS cross-country skier|19}}</ref>

